headline: Carnival Beats Earnings Estimates and Posts Record Revenue. Why the Stock Is Falling.
summary: The cruise operator beats earnings expectations in the first quarter, delivers record revenue and even hikes full-year guidance—all despite mounting fears over consumer demand.

headline: Norwegian Cruise Line rating raised at Morgan Stanley
summary: Investing.com -- Morgan Stanley raised Norwegian Cruise Line (NYSE:NCLH) Holdings to Equal-Weight from Underweight on Friday, citing a more balanced risk-reward profile after recent stock underperformance.

headline: Q4 Earnings Highs And Lows: Norwegian Cruise Line (NYSE:NCLH) Vs The Rest Of The Travel and Vacation Providers Stocks
summary: Quarterly earnings results are a good time to check in on a company’s progress, especially compared to its peers in the same sector. Today we are looking at Norwegian Cruise Line (NYSE:NCLH) and the best and worst performers in the travel and vacation providers industry.
